to.sven.androidrccar.host.accessorycommunication.model

Enum ResponseMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ResponseMessage>
      • to.sven.androidrccar.host.accessorycommunication.model.ResponseMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ResponseMessage>

    public enum ResponseMessage
extends java.lang.Enum<ResponseMessage>
    This enumeration contains response message that can be received from the µController (Car). It contains a message type id and the length of the payload in bytes.
    Author:
    sven

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • REQUEST_OK

        public static final ResponseMessage REQUEST_OK
        The send request was processed and everything is OK. Can only received when expected by the request command. This response may not changed in newer protocol versions!

      • ERROR

        public static final ResponseMessage ERROR
        Something went wrong. Payload: short: A error id want went wrong. See ErrorId for available error types. Exceptional response message: Can received after every request. This response may not changed in newer protocol versions!

      • BATTERY_NEAR_EMPTY

        public static final ResponseMessage BATTERY_NEAR_EMPTY
        The battery power is near empty. The µController does not process any requests. Exceptional response message: Can received after every request. This response may not changed in newer protocol versions!

      • PROTOCOL_VERSION

        public static final ResponseMessage PROTOCOL_VERSION
        Contains the version of the protocol that the µController speaks. Can only received when the RequestCommand.GET_PROTOCOL_VERSION was send. Payload: version as Short: A version number. This response may not changed in newer protocol versions!

      • FEATURES

        public static final ResponseMessage FEATURES
        Contains the features of the car. Payload: first byte: bit 0: adjustableSpeed as Boolean: CarFeatures.adjustableSpeed; bit 1: driveBackward as Boolean: CarFeatures.driveBackward bit 2: batteryPower as Boolean: CarFeatures.batteryPower bit 3-7: unused, can used in future. cameraPanMin as Short: 0 is 0 degree. Short.MAX_VALUE is 180 degree. cameraPanMax as Short: 0 is 0 degree. Short.MAX_VALUE is 180 degree. cameraTiltMin as Short: 0 is 0 degree. Short.MAX_VALUE is 180 degree. cameraTiltMax as Short: 0 is 0 degree. Short.MAX_VALUE is 180 degree. If cameraPanMin and cameraPanMax is both 0 this means that camera pan is not supported. The same applies to camera tilt with cameraTiltMin and cameraTiltMax. Can only received when the RequestCommand.GET_FEATURES was send.

      • BATTERY_STATE

        public static final ResponseMessage BATTERY_STATE
        Contains battery charging level. Payload: chargingLevel as Short: BatteryPowerMessage.chargingLevel 0 is 0% Short.MAX_VALUE is 100% Can only received when the RequestCommand.GET_BATTERY_STATE was send.
